===Etymology 1===
The sense of "safeguard" comes from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|Palladium}} (the image of {{m|en|Pallas}} that protected {{m|en|Troy}}), from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|Παλλάδιον}}, from {{m|grc|Παλλάς}}, an alternative name for {{m|en|Athena}}.

====Noun====
{{en-noun|palladia}}

# A safeguard {{qualifier|from a statue of Athena that was believed to safeguard the ancient city of Troy}}.
#* Blackstone
#*: The trial by jury is the '''Palladium''' of our civil rights.

